  "texts": [
    "• Banking77 (B77) (Casanueva et al., 2020) is a fine-grained dataset designed for intent detection within the banking domain.",
    "It comprises 13,083 customer service queries annotated with 77 unique intents, such as card_arrival and lost_or_stolen_card.",
    "The dataset focuses on single-domain intent classification, providing a granular view of customer queries in the banking sector.",
    "With 10,003 training and 3,080 test examples, Banking77 offers a valuable resource for evaluating machine learning models in intent detection.",
    "The dataset has been curated to fill the gap in existing intent detection datasets, which often feature fewer intents or cover multiple domains without the depth offered here."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}